						<p>On the south wall, <hi rend="italic">mukha-maṇḍapa</hi> of Tirumēṟṟaḷīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 4: 975 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to refer to some gift made to the deity, Tirumēṟṟaḷi uḍaiyār, at Pāchchil in Maḻa-nāḍu by a dancing girl <hi rend="italic">(talaikkōli)</hi> of Karaipputtūr. </p>						

